    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Run the code and observe what happens. \r\n2. Run the test to see if that gives you any insights into the bug.\r\n3. Decide which debugging strategy would be useful for this buggy program. \r\n4. Iteratively refine and test the updates you make to the code.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Unit Guide**\r\n\r\nDocument your experience with this debugging challenge:\r\n- What strategy did you use? \r\n- How did it help?\r\n- When might it be most useful in the future?",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\npainter = Painter()\n\ndef turn_right():\n    painter.turn_left()\n    painter.turn_left()\n    painter.turn_left()\n\ndef paint_path():\n    painter.paint(\"rainbow\")\n    painter.move()\n    painter.turn_right  \n    painter.move()\n    painter.paint(\"rainbow\")\n\npaint_path\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
    "teacher_markdown": "**Error Type**: Logic Error (Incorrect function calls and missing function calls)\r\n\r\n**Expected Outcome**: The `Painter` should turn right and paint a rainbow path.\r\n\r\nDebugging Challenge\r\n\r\n- The first bug is that `turn_right` is a user-defined function, not a `Painter` method, so it shouldn't use dot notation.\r\n- The second bug is that `turn_right` is not being called because it's missing `()`.\r\n- The third bug is that `paint_path` is also not being called because it's missing `()`.\r\n- Hint for students: Functions must be called with parentheses to execute.",
    "display_name": "Debugging Challenge 3",
    "thumbnail_url": "https://images.code.org/8481f3c0ce363c232c7ba7c429e4141a-system.png",
    "bubble_choice_description": "You’ve carefully written instructions for the `Painter`, but it’s acting like it never got the memo. Some actions seem to be missing, and others aren’t happening when they should. Why won’t your `Painter` follow the plan?"
